Witch Spring 3 is so far my favorite of the whole Witch Spring series. A 
lot of improvement from previous games. I just loved it. Story is very 
interesting and cute. I love the big casts in WS3. The localization is 
better too. I also like the battle system better than its predecessors. The 
vitality stone system is also a good replacement for the moonlight system 
from WS2. It could be used to unlock and level up dolls, it can also 
protect and heals you when you're supposed to be dead from an attack. 
Limiting training by using days is a great idea to make sure we don't train 
too much at the beginning, but it practically doesn't mean too much in the 
late game since you can just eat stat-improving items. There are some 
things to improve such as skills of the doll. I rarely used any doll 
besides the boar and a couple other dolls. I guess I train too much, my 
character got too OP lol.

Definitely a worth while sequel to the origional 2, though i feel like some 
of the arias like the desert and mountains and merc camps were lacking 
content, vast open spaces with little to none use but to put a bit of 
distance between you and the villages. I feel like there could atleast be a 
few monsters or enemies in these places. As for the story. Absolutely loved 
it, it was an amazing story with twists and turns all around, catching you 
off guard at times and pulling at your heart strings. Gameplay. I loved the 
gameplay itself, the controls were simple enough and the way you cast and 
use spells and swords were amazing. That being said i still feel there is 
room for improvement, it felt too fast paced to obtain all the items and 
recepies compared to the other games. The dolls were a very refreshing 
addition to the game series and i would love too see this incorporated 
more, maybe even have the ability to customise a single doll yourself with 
various parts. It just wouldnt be a doll maker witch if you couldnt 
actually make a doll in game. Overall, absolutely wonderful game and would 
love too see the series continue. You have a lifelong fan. Summery and 
sugestions Pros >Loving and great story >Great magical abilities that 
really lets you feel the power >Beautiful world >Intence battles and good 
variety of monsters and items. >Well developed characters, really set the 
bar high with this, they really feel the way the team portrated them. 
>Dolls are absolutely amazing, the combat is well thought out and having 3 
at the same time really lets you play the way you want too Cons >Some of 
the arias were lacking content, arias that are huge but have little to no 
use but for maybe one scene or a single enemy >You cant summon most of the 
dolls outside of battle, would love to have a non mounted doll with me 
while i travel like the knight or archer > The end game doesnt really have 
that much content and no real reason to continue playing afterwards, goals 
and missions are confusing and you have to traverse the continent multiple 
times to try and find everything >I feel the variety of dolls were a bit 
limited, you basically received them all for no work, would have loved to 
maybe find a few out in the world instead of them all just being in a room, 
the baby fox being the only exception ofcourse Suggestions >More magic 
capabilities, while you have introduced a new magic skill i feel there is 
much more that could be done, there is a wide range of dark items out 
there, maybe a dark attribute in magic >The dolls were a great inclusion, 
leveling them to make them stronger really made me grimd through this game 
to acheive this. However i would really have loved to maybe have a 
customisable doll ,various part to have some effect on the doll or even 
sets that can be mixed and matched, having a humanoid or even feral base to 
work from, i really think this would be an absolute great adition to the 
doll summoning. >After the game is done the world becomes really sparce and 
feels empty, even more than the actual gameplay since most human enemies 
are gone from the world. I feel these places could have been set up for 
other kinds of monster and maybe even new kinds of monsters to apear in the 
wild since human presence are no longer there. I thank the creators of the 
game that made this, it really is an absolute wonderful game, very few are 
in comparison to this, definitely recomend and well woth the price

It's a cute and fun little game just like the other ones before it. Combat 
is more defined here giving you the new class of 'swordmaster' that 
combines magic with melee, magic animations have true eyecandy effects, 
sadly (for some) you don't get to collect many pets and there are only 3 
endings (good, bad, true). You do get to wake up and upgrade dolls that can 
punch the heck out of your opponents, buff or heal you. My personal 
favorite is Lala since her buffs stack up to a max of 30% random stat 
increase. The one problem that upset me was a strange pathing bug that 
caused Erudi to move around weirdly, skip in place or stutter. Despite the 
poor english, the story is good, Erudi is a cuteand lovable girl and the 
action is better than in the other two games.

I don't know how much longer I can wait for the post game update. Honestly the BEST RPG I've played to date. Started with Witch Spring 2 and immediately bought 3. I really like the improved training system and the goal system as well. Although movement seemed a little wonky at times when compared to the second game, but hey, I still played the game for 30+ hours. Also, I didn't seem to see any odd translations throughout my gameplay as I did in WS2 and DEFINITELY in WS1. This game is also very UNIQUE as I spent countless hours searching for a similar game for mobile that was as good as this game is. The new pet/doll system is quite an improvement from some of WS2's OP pets (Blue). Also, the idea of equipment is pretty good, although a few more options or equipment slots would've been even better. Also, love the soundtrack, some from previous games and more new  songs. Some say this is too easy to beat, but honestly, I like my story-driven RPGs to not be a grinding experience. Overall, absolutely worth the money, 10/10. Wish I could forget the story to experience this again üò´  EDIT : YAAAAAAAASSSSSSSSSSS, POST GAME ADDED, thank you sooo much Kiwiwalks!

I personally think this would've worked better if Eirudy had a opening cut scene explaining her tale. Love how they are all connected and u still have the third continent mentioned in the storyline to continue this awesome adventure. I hate to give cons but the second one was better and heres why. The enemies are kind of lack luster some honestly just look stupid. Another thing I think was cheaped out on was the dialogue pictures of the characters in the second one Luna had dozen or more expressions which made this type of RPG different then others which the same picture used over and other like most old school RPGs. You had a good thing in two with that should have kept it. Also when the terrain ascended or descended the whole screen shook which maybe u where going for more life like physics but who likes looking through a windshield on a bumpy road kind destroys the secenry and point. Lastly in all the games the transition to new areas most aren't labeled and very touchy. More in this one then others I think but a yes or no option telling you where it leads and asking if u want to go would be nice. Another thing that bugged me was the character interaction areas where to wide got stuck talking when I had no need to repeatedly. This one had trouble reaching ingredients too which you have to circle some to find the spot to pick them up. The graphics had some sluppy parts hear and there but the one I hated was the mummies in the vision that was just silly. Sorry guys I had to but don't let it stop you from a fourth let it help you. I love these games please keep them coming.

Okay now that I have finished the entire game I feel like I have something to say about it. First of all, developers you guys really had out done yourselves! This is an excellent game as the previous two! I love the new combat system and all sorts of new storylines and characters However tho, it seems like the entire game ending is based on whether you had trusted the human or not after the dragon fight. I chose to trust them and what it lead to is that I had missed a ton of content and a few character plotlines in the end. I don't mind having major decisions like this. But wouldn't it have came too soon? Like that was the early part of the game and that one button had decided on how the story is going to end‚Ä¶ I feel like you guys should have done something about that, but other than this. The game is perfect IMO! 5 stars as always! Waiting for WS4 already in the last continent!

Once again, another good WitchSpring game. But somehow, I felt this was way too easy. Unlike in witchspring 2, the training system is too easy. All you have to do is wait for the time to elapse so you can train. The monsters were way too easy to kill. You don't even need to create new supporting magic circles because its already saved. Crafting is too easy. There are many areas, yet the quests in each doesn't really affect the story. Please add a post game. I really enjoyed WitchSpring 2 because it was hard. I was so satisfied after finishing it because I worked hard for it. But this, it was okay. I finished in less than 2 days. I am looking forward to doing the other ending, hopefully it will satisfy me. Witchspring 2 was definitely longer than this. Hope you add a post game soon. Thank you for creating this series! *EDIT* Ok, I have finished the dark ending. It was much easier to finish, and it was just ok. I still don't get how I could get through the gate in Shubeth Road. By far, I enjoyed Witchspring 2 more, I just I felt it had a good story. Well I know it is still the same intro as this game, but I didn't enjoy it quite that much. I am looking forward for Witchspring 4 if it will happen, thank you again! I believe Johannes said there were 3 continents?
